    {
      "id": "68",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Azhdaha",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/29/237301566/c6b12865e76b20df8ba7c121d47be54a_2672735058154713363.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Most of the ancient Geo life forms that live below Liyue are blind, having not seen the sunlight for an age. For millennia, the rock’s spirit slumbered in Nantianmen, seeming not at all unlike the surrounding hills. But when it awakened, even the tiniest movement or the slightest stretch would cause the earth to tremble and shake. Once, Rex Lapis was walking alone in the mountains. He hears a remote voice unlike any other coming from a crack in the earth. The voice was sometimes sad and songlike; other times, it was loud and thunderous. The Lord of Geo searched here and there before finally unearthing a strange stone from the bedrock.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/29/237301566/4665e61d5418b7195e79828a1247d27f_4347904696464214544.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Lord of Geo took pity on the rock's spirit and carved it into a vivid representation of a dragon. That's how Azhdaha was. Rex Lapis answered his wish and took him above ground. With his finger, he bestowed the dragon with a pair of eyes to see the world and came to an agreement with him. Rex Lapis agreed to let Azhdaha live among the people above ground. But if the day ever came when he brought ruin to order, he would once again be sealed in the dark. The dragon accompanied the Lord of Geo, fighting campaigns alongside him in four corners of the world.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"The crash of a spear brought billowing dust, the mountains and waters made way at the sound. The sight of a dragon bestowed with a touch, the promise of rainwater blessing the ground.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/29/237301566/675c4c8064b42f7e98de36913976357a_8707406021498438587.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "For many centuries, Azhdaha, together with Morax and other Adepti, helped the people of Liyue. However, the memories of rocks do not last long. Those memories that survive are rooted in powerful emotion. But as time passes, so these memories fade into obscurity. Erosion, an inevitable Teyvat's order, is the world’s greatest destroyer of memories. Erosion ground Azhdaha's consciousness into oblivion. Slowly, he forgot the face of his old friend, and his memories of defending Liyue Harbor disintegrated. Azhdaha, now incomplete, became irascible and aggressive. Erosion made him even more savage, and no matter how he struggled, he lost the ability to coexist with humanity and lost all reason. Morax shared some of his power with Azhdaha to prevent further erosion, but it was futile. It is the natural order, an unstoppable force.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/29/237301566/884f5f6baa32c6d7b021900c1850c30e_2990351017302664137.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Overexploitation of the mines caused the Ley Lines in the Chasm to quake, which brought untold suffering to Azhdaha. One day, he attacked the Chasm and waged war against Morax. Rex Lapis had to fight with his friend. He chose justice but did not forsake his kindness. He came to Azhdaha not as an assassin, so Azhdaha was willingly sealed away. Morax imprisoned Azhdaha underground, placing a seal protecting the passage.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/29/237301566/1fb1e07343f31e966670941818cbae18_3545662994285643079.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Millennia later, the seal restraining Azhdaha loosened, and his power manifested in this world as a child named Jiu. With this new identity, he was able to vent about the forces that suppressed him. Azhdaha decided to launch the attack from outside and within to fully destroy the seal. Azhdaha hypnotized miners to dig a tunnel to the sealed entrance. At the same time, another power, the remnants of Azhdaha's benevolence, awakened due to the loosening of the seal. This power was too weak to reincarnate but strong enough to possess the human body of Kun Jun. His only aim was to find Morax and aid him in stopping Jiu. These powers were polarities and the schism of the will of Azhdaha. Jiu was the memory of the earth, while Kun Jun was the memory of coexistence with humanity and the last contract Azhdaha had with Morax. Thanks to \"Kun Jun,\" Azhdaha was able to reminisce about his time with the Lord of Geo and their friendship and contract. Before disappearing, he thanked Morax and said he wouldn’t forget how Morax gave him eyes when Azhdaha was yearning for the sun.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"All powers under heaven, rise and fall of land and sea…",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "...A star appears within the wild... a sun ascends as bright as... jade…\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"In the wilderness, snow falls on a spring day. In an instant, it will melt. Even where it is fleeting and leaves no trace. Even where it will never fall again…\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
